  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nDealers are actively buying this dip as SPX sits right at the massive -116B gamma wall at 6570, creating strong technical support from forced dealer long hedging. The breakout regime with concentrated negative gamma walls from 6560-6580 means any bounce will face amplified selling pressure as dealers hedge short gamma positions, while a break below 6570 triggers cascading dealer buying down to the 6565/6560 levels. Watch 6570 as the critical pivot - hold here for a bounce toward dealer selling at 6600, but a decisive break unleashes the negative gamma cascade toward 6560 with dealers as momentum buyers.",
